# Kiro Patchwork - environment variable EXAMPLE
#
# This file contains NO real secrets. It documents the environment variables
# Patchwork uses, with placeholder values only. Copy it to a local ".env"
# (which is gitignored and never committed) and put your REAL values there:
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# Configuration is via environment variables only - no secrets are baked into
# mcp.json or any committed file. Only ".env" holds real values, and it stays
# untracked.

# --- Engine configuration (non-secret) -------------------------------------

# Default workspace directory the Patchwork engine and MCP server read. This is
# the real, non-secret default (mcp.json sets the same value); a per-call
# `workspace` argument overrides it. Safe to commit as-is.
PATCHWORK_WORKSPACE=patchwork

# --- Model provider API keys (secrets - real values go in your .env) --------
#
# The three Patchwork agents run on two model families, so a bring-your-own-key
# setup needs the matching provider key. These are commented out because the
# engine itself never reads them - uncomment only the ones your model
# configuration requires, and set the REAL values in your local .env, not here.

# patchwork-sre and patchwork-scribe run on the Claude family (claude-sonnet-4):
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=<your-anthropic-api-key>

# patchwork-reviewer runs on a different family, GLM (glm-5) via z.ai:
# ZAI_API_KEY=<your-zai-api-key>
